cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.CV, cs.AI 

The paper discusses the stochastic training of artificial neural networks, which is a topic closely related to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The use of differential equations to analyze the behavior of residual networks and their variants suggests a systems and control theory perspective (cs.SY). The experiments conducted on a real-world image classification task indicate a computer vision (cs.CV) application, while the proposed method for utilizing Bernoulli dropout within the plain residual network architecture suggests an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) approach.
